        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 11 at 4:03PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 403 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 31
miles north of Ute Park, or 26 miles west of Raton, moving south at
10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Vermejo Park.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
